\ref 294
\ELANBegin 476.424
\ELANEnd 477.828
\ELANParticipant Gildo
\tx de  odi ini  de  k'ate ini  /                        
\orth de      ini  de  k'ate ini                           
\glt la      malu la  laran   moras malu                  
\glm NEG     baku NEG rasa  terluka baku                  
\gle NEG     RCP  NEG feel hurt RCP                       
\glp NEG     RCP  NEG mágoa RCP                           
\tlt Hodi ita la odi malu no la hirus malu.               
\tlm Supaya kita tidak saling dendam.                     
\tle So that we won't hold grudges amongst ourselves.     
\tlp Assim para não guardamos o ódio entre nós.           
\dt 14/Jul/2004                                          
\cm by sacrificing dogs in that place they attempt to get rid of their quarrels/keep peace in the village. This is still done once a year in Derowake (close to MariaAngelas house). The event is called /thunu kai-we'e/ "bakar ?pagar?". People generally bring dogs that have been misbehaving (killing chicken, attacking people, and the like). Around 20 dogs are killed in this way each year (hitting them on the head (with a /kai-n'ete), probably breaking their neck, no longer by cutting their throat) MariaAngelas extended family (which includes Hermenegildo, Dario (perikanan), Joao (from the belis recordings), Aleixo) is allowed to kill dogs only at this event and at no other time in the year; other families occasionally kill dogs for meat, often used as a snack to go with drinking. MariaAngelas extended family derives magic powers (punya kelebihan) from the ritual/dogs. When in a serious conflict with people from other villages, they have the ability to speak "atas nama anjing" - and when they do that, no one dares to oppose them any longer. Whoever were to dare them, will spit blood (muntah darah) without obivous external influence. This only works in case of serious conflict and after they have held secret ceremonies in their house. They don't use this power in Caisido. Note that they are not Liurai in Caisido, but they are certainly an influential family (possibly one of the two most influential families together with Waihau (Orlando, Manuel, NahaSusu, MetaUsa, Jose Antonio (wartawan), etc.) - both also are richer than most other families which is shown by the fact that they have many members with higher education (Heremenegildo is a health worker, etc.). Waihau has snake (ular) and bat (kelelewar) as "totem" animals. They kill a goat and feed it to snakes (wild ones). In Baahuu there is a similar family (Maukali) who derives magic powers from dogs. The dog ritual is different from rau-wai which is also held by Derowake. Snake and dog are the only animals singled out for these special occasions, nothing similar for goats, crocodiles, horses, buffalo, fish, etc.
 

